# $Id$

<p>This special supplement to Debian Weekly News is a review of the
most important happenings of 2003 in the Debian community.  This is
certainly not a comprehensive list. The focus is on unusual and
notable events, not the continual background development activity and
discussions.</p>

# Last Bug in 2002:  174882
# Last Bug in 2003: ~225393
# (- 225393 174882) 50511

<p>To give some idea of the sheer volume of what has gone on behind the scenes
this year, a few numbers: Nearly 200 security advisories have been issued,
about 50 thousand bug reports were filed this year, in total about 180
thousand messages were sent to the bug tracking system, 422 thousand messages
were posted to the various Debian mailing lists, the English DWN source used
about 750&nbsp;kB and the Debian project attended about 40 events.</p>

<p>Here are the most memorable events of 2003 in the Debian community:</p>

<p><b>January</b></p>

<ul>

<li> Peter Karlsson <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-www-0212/msg00388.html">\
     implemented</a> ICS files (Internet Calendar entries) for all future
     events.

<li> Andrew Cosgriff created an <a
     href="http://polydistortion.net/urls/new-debian-packages.rss">RSS</a>
     feed of new Debian packages.

<li> Nils Lohner <a
     href="http://lists.spi-inc.org/pipermail/spi-announce/2003/000034.html">\
     resigned</a> as president of <a href="http://www.spi-inc.org/">Software
     in the Public Interest</a> (SPI) and Ean Schuessler was <a
     href="http://www.spi-inc.org/corporate/resolutions/resolution-2002-12-17.wta.2">\
     appointed</a> as new vice president.

<li> The <a href="$(HOME)/ports/amd64/">x86-64</a> Port of Debian was <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-devel-0301/msg00453.html">\
     started</a>.

<li> The <a
     href="http://www.xboxdeveloper.net/index.php?mode=viewproj&amp;id=245">\
     Dreamix</a> project brought Debian GNU/Linux to the X-box.

<li> Santiago García Mantinan <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-boot-0301/msg00386.html">\
     announced</a> weekly created network-installation CD images for sarge.

<li> Debian GNU/Linux received the award "<a href="$(HOME)/misc/awards">best
     budget choice</a>" of the Swedish computer magazine <a
     href="http://mikrodatorn.idg.se/">Mikrodatorn</a>.

</ul>

<p><b>February</b></p>

<ul>

<li> Debian was <a href="http://fsm2003.softwarelivre.org/">represented</a> at
     the World Social Forum in Brazil by <a
     href="http://www.debian-rs.org/">Debian-RS</a>, a local Debian users
     group.

<li> The Debian project <a href="$(HOME)/News/2003/20030207">announced</a>
     that it is a founding member of the new <a
     href="http://www.desktoplinuxconsortium.org/">Desktop Linux
     Consortium</a>.

<li> Debian GNU/Linux <a
     href="http://www.linuxdevices.com/articles/AT9943738185.html">powers</a>
     the PRISMIQ <a href="http://www.prismiq.com/products/">MediaPlayer</a>, a
     networked entertainment gateway.

<li> The <a href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-multimedia/">Debian
     Multimedia</a> sub-project was started after <a
     href="http://www.demudi.org/">DeMuDi</a> has reached release 0.9 in order
     to combine the efforts of <a
     href="http://fsfeurope.org/projects/agnula/">A GNU/Linux Audio
     Distribution</a> and Debian.

<li> Lars Wirzenius <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-project-0302/msg00001.html">discovered</a>
     that 769 keys of Debian developers are strongly connected.

<li> The <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-devel-announce-0302/msg00010.html">\
     results</a> from the security <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-devel-announce-0211/msg00001.html">\
     survey</a> last year were published.

<li> <a href="http://www.spi-inc.org/">Software in the Public Interest,
     Inc.</a> announced <a
     href="http://www.spi-inc.org/secretary/votes/vote1/BrucePerens.xhtml">Bruce
     Perens</a>, <a
     href="http://www.spi-inc.org/secretary/votes/vote1/JohnGoerzen.xhtml">John
     Goerzen</a>, and <a
     href="http://www.spi-inc.org/secretary/votes/vote1/MakoHill.xhtml">Benj. Mako
     Hill</a> as new Board members after an election.

</ul>

<p><b>March</b></p>

<ul>

<li> Matthias Klose <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-devel-0303/msg00025.html">called</a>
     for testing of the upcoming GNU Compiler Collection (GCC) 3.3
     with real-world applications.

<li> Mario Lang <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-accessibility-0302/msg00000.html">\
     started</a> the debian-accessibility effort.

<li> Finally, all components of KDE 3.1.1 have been accepted into the
     unstable (sid) archive.

</ul>

<p><b>April</b></p>

<ul>

<li> Martin Michlmayr <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-devel-announce-0303/msg00025.html">won</a>
     the project leader <a href="$(HOME)/vote/2002/vote_0001">election</a>.

<li> Raphaël Hertzog, Wichert Akkerman, and Roland Mas <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-devel-announce-0303/msg00024.html">\
     announced</a> <a href="http://alioth.debian.org/">Alioth</a>, the
     Debian installation of GForge.

<li> Mario Lang <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-accessibility-0303/msg00026.html">\
     managed</a> to do a complete installation with the brltty enabled
     debian-installer disk.

<li> Enrico Zini <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-devel-0304/msg00127.html">announced</a>
     the birth of the <a
     href="http://deb-usability.alioth.debian.org/">Debian Usability
     Research</a> effort focused on identifying and addressing
     Debian-specific usability issues.

<li> The port of Debian to the <a href="$(HOME)/ports/amd64/">\
     AMD64</a> architecture was started.

<li> Anthony Towns proposed a <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-legal-0304/msg00246.html">\
     statement</a> on the <a
     href="http://www.gnu.org/copyleft/fdl.html">GNU Free
     Documentation License</a>.

</ul>

<p><b>May</b></p>

<ul>

<li> Support for the old 80386 on which Linux was started, is ceased,
     due to GCC 3.2 and the new libstdc++5 library requiring an 80486
     processor or higher.

<li> The DDTP team and the Debian-BR project <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-devel-announce-0304/msg00015.html">\
     announced</a> the first public release of APT with <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-devel-announce-0210/msg00004.html">\
     support</a> for translated package descriptions.

<li> Enrico Zini <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-devel-0304/msg02167.html">announced</a>
     Debian package tags (also known as keywords or categories) which
     are thought as the evolution of the package sections historically
     used in Debian systems.

<li> Robert Millan <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-bsd-0305/msg00002.html">\
     announced</a> that his GNU/FreeBSD chroot jail is finally
     self-hosting and that he was able to build working packages of
     glibc 2.3, GCC 3.2.3 and binutils inside the jail.

<li> Daniel K. Gebhart <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-devel-0305/msg00756.html">\
     announced</a> the <a href="http://mentors.debian.net/">Debian Mentors
     Project</a> which implements a package repository for not yet accepted
     developers.

</ul>

<p><b>June</b></p>

<ul>

<li> Dirk Eddelbüttel <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-devel-0305/msg02037.html">\
     announced</a> <a
     href="http://dirk.eddelbuettel.com/quantian.html">Quantian</a>, a
     re-mastered version of <a
     href="http://www.knopper.net/knoppix/">Knoppix</a> to support
     applied or theoretical workers in quantitative or data-driven
     fields.

<li> Slashdot <a
     href="http://slashdot.org/articles/03/05/29/1336229.shtml">\
     reported</a> about an effort by Wim Vandersmissen who created <a
     href="http://bofh.be/clusterknoppix/">ClusterKnoppix</a> which
     features the openMosix terminal server, openMosix autodiscovery,
     and cluster management tools such as openMosix userland.

<li> Colin Watson <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-devel-0305/msg02174.html">\
     announced</a> two new tags for the <a href="$(HOME)/Bugs/">Bug
     Tracking System</a>.

<li> Branden Robinson <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-x-0306/msg00039.html">\
     announced</a> that Debian's XFree86 packages are becoming
     team-maintained.

<li> Robert Millan <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-bsd-0306/msg00002.html">\
     announced</a> that he has managed to get <a
     href="http://people.debian.org/~rmh/gnu-freebsd/">\
     GNU/FreeBSD</a> installed self-hosting.

<li> Andrew Greenberg and Brian O'Neel from the Portland State
     Aerospace Society <a
     href="http://www.wired.com/news/culture/0,1284,59144,00.html">built</a>
     a 12 pound <a
     href="http://twiki.psas.pdx.edu/bin/view/PSAS/Projects">suborbital
     rocket</a> which uses <a
     href="http://twiki.psas.pdx.edu/bin/view/PSAS/Usenix2003Paper">Free
     Software</a>, such as Debian.

</ul>

<p><b>July</b></p>

<ul>

<li> Mako Hill <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-devel-announce-0307/msg00002.html">\
     announced</a> the <a href="http://nonprofit.debian.net/">Debian
     non-profit</a> sub-project.

<li> The Debian project maintained a one day <a
     href="http://www.infodrom.org/Debian/events/LinuxTag2003/day.html">\
     conference</a> dedicated to Debian people at this years' <a
     href="$(HOME)/events/2003/0710-linuxtag">LinuxTag</a> in
     Karlsruhe, targeting advanced users and developers.

<li> Michel Grentzinger opened <a
     href="http://bugs.debian.org/200000">Bug #200000</a>.

<li> Unexpectedly many Debian developers and users participated in
     this years' <a href="$(HOME)/events/2003/0718-debconf">Debian
     conference</a> and the first debcamp at the University of Oslo.

<li> Barak Pearlmutter <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-legal-0307/msg00122.html">\
     composed</a> a draft Debian Free Software Guidelines (DFSG) <a
     href="http://people.debian.org/~bap/dfsg-faq.html">FAQ</a>.

<li> James Patten and Ben Recht <a
     href="http://www.linuxdevices.com/news/NS3340861719.html">\
     developed</a> a composition and performance <a
     href="http://web.media.mit.edu/~jpatten/audiopad/">instrument</a>
     <a href="http://web.media.mit.edu/~jpatten/audiopad/apfaq.html">\
     based</a> on Knoppix.

<li> Support for the PowerPC architecture was added to to <a
     href="http://www.knopper.net/knoppix">Knoppix</a> during <a
     href="http://www.linuxtag.org/2003/de/conferences/talk.xsp?id=59">\
     LinuxTag</a>.

</ul>

<p><b>August</b></p>

<ul>

<li> The Debian project <a
     href="http://www.debconf.org/10years/">celebrated</a> its 10th
     birthday at several locations worldwide.

<li> The <a href="http://www.lpi.org/">Linux Professional
     Institute</a> introduced new exams which allow candidates to be
     tested on RPM or Debian package management.

<li> <a href="http://www.mepis.org/">Mepis Linux</a> is a LiveCD
     derived from the Debian GNU/Linux code base.

</ul>

<p><b>September</b></p>

<ul>

<li> The Debian project has <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-amd64-0308/msg00035.html">received</a>
     full access to a Dual Opteron <a
     href="http://db.debian.org/machines.cgi?host=pergolesi">machine</a>
     for <a href="$(HOME)/ports/amd64/">porting</a> efforts.

<li> Carlos Laviola <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-devel-announce-0308/msg00003.html">\
     announced</a> that the Debian Conference #4 will be held in <a
     href="http://www.uoregon.edu/~sergiok/brasil/portoalegre.html">Porto
     Alegre</a>, Brazil.

<li> Mattias Wadenstein <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-mirrors-0309/msg00000.html">\
     announced</a> the new <a
     href="http://cdimage.debian.org/debian-cd/">cdimage.debian.org</a>
     with iso images and an authoritative directory structure.

<li> Martin Michlmayr <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-project-0309/msg00020.html">reported</a>
     that Skolelinux has gained some funding in Norway.

<li> Andreas Schuldei <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-devel-announce-0309/msg00011.html">\
     announced</a> that the <a
     href="http://www.skolelinux.no/">Skolelinux</a> project and the
     <a href="http://wiki.debian.net/DebianEdu">Debian-Edu</a>
     sub-project will merge.

<li> The first debian-installer <a
     href="http://people.debian.org/~pere/debian-installer/di-debcamp-2003-1.html">\
     work camp</a> took place in <a
     href="http://oldenburger.linuxtage.de/Oldenburg2003/">Oldenburg</a>,
     Germany.

<li> Bruce Perens <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-legal-0309/msg01309.html">\
     organised</a> people from the <a href="http://www.fsf.org">Free
     Software Foundation</a> and Debian to discuss issues revolving
     around the GNU <a href="http://www.gnu.org/copyleft/fdl.html">\
     Free Documentation License</a>.

</ul>

<p><b>October</b></p>

<ul>

<li> Debian has won the <a
     href="http://pr.linuxjournal.com/article.php?sid=785">Linux
     Journal 2003 Readers' Choice Award</a> in the category of "Favourite
     Distribution".

<li> Martin Michlmayr <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-devel-announce-0310/msg00003.html">\
     reported</a> about the formation of a trademark committee.

<li> Debian has won the <a
     href="http://www.linuxenterprise.de/itr/service/show.php3?id=104&amp;nodeid=35">\
     Linux Enterprise Reader's Choice Award 2003</a> in the category
     "Best Enterprise Distribution".

<li> Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, contains a long <a
     href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Debian">entry</a> about the
     Debian project and its distribution.


<li> Debian has won the <a
     href="http://www.linux-magazin.de/Artikel/ausgabe/2003/12/award/award.html">\
     Linux New Media Award 2003</a> in the category "Best
     Distribution".

</ul>

<p><b>November</b></p>

<ul>

<li> Branden Robinson <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-vote-0310/msg00106.html">\
     proposed</a> to amend the <a
     href="$(HOME)/social_contract">social contract</a>.

<li> Manoj Srivastava <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-project-0310/msg00178.html">\
     proposed</a> writing a <a
     href="http://people.debian.org/~srivasta/Position_Statement.html">\
     document</a> that attempts to address some concerns that members
     of the Debian project have about the GNU <a
     href="http://www.gnu.org/copyleft/fdl.html">Free Documentation
     License</a>.

<li> Ben Armstrong <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-devel-announce-0311/msg00000.html">\
     announced</a> that <a href="$(HOME)/devel/debian-jr/">Debian
     Jr.</a> joined the <a href="http://www.osef.org/">Open Source
     Education Foundation</a>.

<li> The second update to Debian 3.0 (r2) was <a
     href="$(HOME)/News/2003/20031121a">released</a>.

<li> The Debian project had to <a
     href="$(HOME)/News/2003/20031121">report</a> that four servers
     were <a
     href="http://cert.uni-stuttgart.de/files/fw/debian-security-20031121.txt">\
     compromised</a> by an unknown attacker.

<li> Wichert Akkerman <a
     href="http://lists.spi-inc.org/pipermail/spi-announce/2003/000064.html">\
     announced</a> the three winners of the Board <a
     href="http://www.spi-inc.org/secretary/">election</a>: David
     Graham, Ian Jackson and Martin 'Joey' Schulze.

</ul>

<p><b>December</b></p>

<ul>

<li> Ian Murdock <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-devel-0312/msg00097.html">\
     reported</a> that unofficial sarge-based iso images using the
     Anaconda installer are offered by <a
     href="http://platform.progeny.com/anaconda/">Progeny</a>.

<li> Anders Salomon <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-devel-0312/msg00070.html">\
     started</a> the Debian Enterprise sub-project.

<li> Bruce Perens <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-devel-0312/msg00196.html">\
     announced</a> the first pass of a UserLinux <a
     href="http://userlinux.com/white_paper.html">white paper</a>.

<li> Javier Fernández-Sanguino Peña <a
     href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-project-0312/msg00044.html">reported</a>
     that a legal Spanish Debian organisation has been founded during
     <a href="http://www.hispalinux.es/~amaya/debconf-es/">\
     DebConf-ES</a> by more than 20 people.

</ul>

<p>As Debian Weekly News enters its sixth year, we would like to thank
everybody who contributed to DWN in the past.  Special thanks also go
to the hoard of translators who make DWN available in a dozen
languages.  And finally, thanks to everyone in the Debian community
for providing such a plethora of interesting discussions, events, and
hard work for us to report on.</p>

